@@ -0,0 +1,211 @@
+# False Positive Analysis: CVE-2025-49124
+
+## Package Under Review
+
+| Field          | Value                                      |
+|----------------|--------------------------------------------|
+| Package        | `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core` |
+| Version        | `10.1.39`                                  |
+| Group ID       | `org.apache.tomcat.embed`                  |
+| Artifact ID    | `tomcat-embed-core`                        |
+| Source Repo    | https://github.com/apache/tomcat.git       |
+| Source Ref     | `10.1.39`                                  |
+| Build Tool     | Apache Ant                                 |
+| Java Version   | 17                                         |
+| Build Target   | `deploy`                                   |
+
+---
+
+## CVE Summary
+
+| Field          | Value                                                              |
+|----------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
+| CVE ID         | CVE-2025-49124                                                     |
+| CWE            | CWE-426 — Untrusted Search Path                                    |
+| Severity       | **Low** (per Apache Tomcat Security Advisory)                      |
+| Affected Component | Apache Tomcat Windows Standalone Installer                     |
+| Vulnerable File | `res/install-win/tomcat.nsi`                                      |
+| Fixed In       | 10.1.42, 11.0.8, 9.0.106                                          |
+| Upstream Fix Commit | `e0e07812224d327a321babb554f5a5758d30cc49`                   |
+| NVD Reference  | https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-49124                   |
+
+**Description:**
+During installation, the Apache Tomcat Windows installer used `icacls.exe` without
+specifying its full system path. This enabled a side-loading (untrusted search path)
+vulnerability where a malicious `icacls.exe` placed earlier in the `PATH` could be
+executed instead of the legitimate Windows system binary.
+
+---
+
+## Verdict
+
+> **FALSE POSITIVE** — CVE-2025-49124 does not affect `tomcat-embed-core`.
+> The vulnerable file (`res/install-win/tomcat.nsi`) is not part of the
+> `tomcat-embed-core` build output and is never shipped in the artifact.
+
+---
+
+## Detailed Justification
+
+### 1. What the Vulnerability Actually Affects
+
+CVE-2025-49124 is scoped exclusively to the **Apache Tomcat Windows Standalone
+Installer** — the `.exe` file distributed for manual Windows installation of the
+Tomcat server.
+
+The vulnerable code is located in a single NSIS installer script:
+
+```
+res/install-win/tomcat.nsi
+```
+
+This file is an NSIS (Nullsoft Scriptable Install System) script. It is used only
+to build the Windows `.exe` installer package. The vulnerability exists in these
+three lines within that script:
+
+```nsis
+; BEFORE fix (vulnerable)
+nsExec::ExecToStack 'icacls "$INSTDIR" /inheritance:r /grant ...'
+nsExec::ExecToStack 'icacls "$INSTDIR\tomcat.ico" /inheritance:e /grant ...'
+nsExec::ExecToStack 'icacls "$INSTDIR\Uninstall.exe" /inheritance:e /grant ...'
+
+; AFTER fix (safe)
+nsExec::ExecToStack '$SYSDIR\icacls "$INSTDIR" /inheritance:r /grant ...'
+nsExec::ExecToStack '$SYSDIR\icacls "$INSTDIR\tomcat.ico" /inheritance:e /grant ...'
+nsExec::ExecToStack '$SYSDIR\icacls "$INSTDIR\Uninstall.exe" /inheritance:e /grant ...'
+```
+
+The vulnerability is triggered **only during the Windows installation process** — not
+at application runtime, not during server startup, and not via any network request.
+
+---
+
+### 2. What `tomcat-embed-core` Is
+
+`tomcat-embed-core` is the **embedded Tomcat Java library**, designed to be used as
+a dependency in Java applications such as Spring Boot. It provides the core Tomcat
+servlet container as a set of Java classes packaged into a JAR file.
+
+The artifact contains:
+- Java `.class` files (compiled from `java/org/apache/...`)
+- Resource files for the servlet container
+- No platform-specific installer scripts
+- No NSIS scripts
+- No `.exe` or `.bat` files related to installation
+
+The `tomcat-embed-core` JAR is a **pure Java library** that runs inside a JVM. It
+has no dependency on or relationship to `icacls.exe` or any Windows installer mechanism.
+
+---
+
+### 3. Build Process Analysis
+
+The source repository (`https://github.com/apache/tomcat.git` at ref `10.1.39`) does
+contain `res/install-win/tomcat.nsi`. However, this file is **not processed** during
+the `tomcat-embed-core` build.
+
+The Ant build system (`build.xml`) separates build targets clearly:
+
+| Build Target             | What it builds                          | Includes `tomcat.nsi`? |
+|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------|------------------------|
+| `deploy` (embed modules) | `tomcat-embed-core` JAR and related JARs | **No**                |
+| `installer` / `release`  | Windows `.exe` installer                | Yes                    |
+
+Running `ant deploy` for `modules: ["org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core"]`
+compiles and packages only the Java source files under `java/org/apache/tomcat/`.
+The `res/install-win/` directory is entirely ignored during this process.
+
+**The output artifact (`tomcat-embed-core-10.1.39.jar`) contains no content from
+`res/install-win/tomcat.nsi` — not in compiled form, not as a resource, not at all.**
+
+---
+
+### 4. Runtime Analysis
+
+Even hypothetically, `tomcat-embed-core` cannot be affected by this vulnerability
+at runtime because:
+
+1. **`icacls.exe` is a Windows file permission tool** — it has no role in the
+   operation of an embedded Java web server.
+2. **The embedded Tomcat library never calls `icacls.exe`** — it manages its
+   internal state entirely through Java APIs.
+3. **The vulnerability window is installation-time only** — it requires the attacker
+   to pre-place a malicious binary before the installer runs. An embedded library
+   has no installer.
+4. **Embedded Tomcat runs inside a JVM** — there is no installation phase where
+   `PATH`-based executable resolution occurs.
+
+---
+
+### 5. Scope of Affected Deployments
+
+Per the Apache Tomcat security advisory, the following are affected:
+
+| Deployment Type                        | Affected? | Reason                                      |
+|----------------------------------------|-----------|---------------------------------------------|
+| Windows standalone installer (`.exe`)  | **Yes**   | Uses `icacls.exe` via NSIS during install   |
+| Linux/macOS standalone installation    | **No**    | `icacls.exe` is Windows-only                |
+| `tomcat-embed-core` Maven artifact     | **No**    | File not present in artifact                |
+| Spring Boot application                | **No**    | Uses embedded Tomcat, no installer involved |
+| Docker/container deployment            | **No**    | No Windows installer involved               |
+
+---
+
+### 6. Scanner False Positive Explanation
+
+Vulnerability scanners flagging `tomcat-embed-core@10.1.39` for CVE-2025-49124
+are doing so because:
+
+- The CVE is associated with **Apache Tomcat versions 10.1.0–10.1.41** broadly
+- Scanners match on **package name + version range** without distinguishing between
+  the standalone server and the embedded library artifact
+- The NVD entry does not explicitly exclude `tomcat-embed-core` from the affected
+  package list
+
+This is a **known limitation of version-range-based CVE matching**. The correct
+determination requires artifact-level analysis, not just version comparison.
+
+---
+
+### 7. Severity Reassessment
+
+The pipeline report assigned **CVSS 8.4 (HIGH)** to this CVE. This is incorrect.
+
+Apache Tomcat's own security advisory rates CVE-2025-49124 as **Low severity** for
+the following reasons:
+
+- The attacker must already have **write access** to a directory in the system `PATH`
+  before the attack can succeed
+- The vulnerability window is **limited to the installation period** only
+- Gaining that level of pre-existing access already represents a significant
+  system compromise
+
+For `tomcat-embed-core`, the effective severity is **None (0.0)** — the attack
+surface does not exist in this artifact.
+
+---
+
+## Conclusion
+
+CVE-2025-49124 is a **false positive** for `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core@10.1.39`.
+
+- The vulnerable file (`res/install-win/tomcat.nsi`) is an NSIS Windows installer script.
+- It is present in the source repository but is **never compiled into or shipped with** the `tomcat-embed-core` artifact.
+- The embedded Tomcat library has no installation phase, makes no calls to `icacls.exe`, and cannot be exploited via this attack vector.
+- No patch is required for `tomcat-embed-core`.
+- This CVE should be suppressed/exempted for this package in the vulnerability scanner.
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- Apache Tomcat Security Advisory: https://tomcat.apache.org/security-10.html
+- NVD Entry: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-49124
+- Upstream Fix Commit (10.1.x): https://github.com/apache/tomcat/commit/e0e07812224d327a321babb554f5a5758d30cc49
+- CWE-426 (Untrusted Search Path): https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/426.html
+
+---
